Install python
Install Homebrew: If you don't have Homebrew installed, open the Terminal app 
(you can find it in the Utilities folder in Applications or use Spotlight search). 
Then, copy and paste the following command and press Enter:
<pre>``` brew install python 
 /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)" ``` </pre>
